        <div id="page-intro-top"></div>
        <div id="page-intro">
            <h1>Cross-project bug tracking.</h1>
                <p>
                    <img src="images/api/main-image.jpg" alt="Collaborate with free software communities." />
                </p>
                <p class="intro-text">
                    <strong>Sharing code means sharing bugs&#58; issues found in free software may originate in code upstream or downstream in a distribution&rsquo;s packaging.</strong> Launchpad tracks how each bug affects different communities and helps you work across project boundaries to find a fix.
                </p>
        </div>
        <div id="page-intro-bottom"></div>
        <ul id="secondary-navigation">
            <li class="button-next">
                <a href="index" tabindex="13" accesskey="d">Next</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div id="further-information">
            <div class="furthur-information-block">
                <div class="furthur-information-block-top"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-mid">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h3>Shared bug reports, independent statuses</h3>
                        <h4>By sharing bug reports and their comment histories across communities, Launchpad lets everyone who&rsquo;s interested work together to find a fix.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/bugs.jpg" alt="By sharing bug reports and their comment histories across communities, Launchpad lets everyone who&rsquo;s interested work together to find a fix" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Each group - whether projects or distributions - can track how the bug affects them by recording their own own status, importance and assignee.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block odd">
                        <h3>Bugs fixed elsewhere</h3>
                        <h4>Your bug may be tracked outside of Launchpad, such as in another project&rsquo;s Bugzilla or Trac.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/tracking.jpg" alt="Your bug may be tracked outside of Launchpad, such as in another project&rsquo;s Bugzilla or Trac" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Launchpad can import bug statuses from external trackers directly into your bug report. There&rsquo;s even a &ldquo;Bugs fixed elsewhere&rdquo; report that shows which of your bugs are marked fixed in external trackers.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-bot"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="furthur-information-block">
                <div class="furthur-information-block-top"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-mid">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h3>Found a fix? Upload a branch</h3>
                        <h4>You no longer need to swap patches in bug comments.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/bugs.jpg" alt="You no longer need to swap patches in bug comments" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Instead, link bug reports to code branches that contain proposed fixes. Download the branch and test it without the hassle of applying patches. Thanks to Bazaar, it&rsquo;s easy to merge bug fix branches into your project&rsquo;s trunk.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block odd">
                        <h3>Bug supervisor</h3>
                        <h4>Delegate day to day bug management to trusted members of your project community.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/tracking.jpg" alt="Delegate day to day bug management to trusted members of your project community" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Assign the Bug Supervisor role to an individual or team who can help plan work on bugs by targeting them to future milestones, setting reserved bug statuses and dealing with private bugs. Appoint a Security Contact to handle bugs marked as security issues.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-bot"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="furthur-information-block singular">
                <div class="furthur-information-block-top"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-mid">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h3>Manage bugs by email</h3>
                        <h4>Launchpad sends email updates to everyone involved in a bug, such as the reporter and assignee.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/bugs.jpg" alt="Launchpad sends email updates to everyone involved in a bug, such as the reporter and assignee" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            You can also subscribe to individual bugs or all the bugs associated with a particular project or distribution package. Bug mail goes both ways&#58; file new bugs, make comments, update statuses, add attachments and more by email. All you need is a GPG key.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="clear"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-bot"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
